From: kerndbox <kerndbox@mixos.io>
Subject: [PATCH 18/18] um: embed UML helper utilities inside kernel ELF

Re-implement Jeff Dike's original 2.4-era mechanism of embedding helper
binaries (port-helper, uml_switch) inside the UML kernel ELF as a data
section, extracted to a tmpdir at startup.

This means a single kernel-ARCH binary is fully self-contained:
  ./linux ubd0=disk.img root=/dev/ubda mem=512M
works without any host-side package installation.

Mechanism:
  1. Build scripts compile helpers as static ELFs, gzip them
  2. objcopy --add-section .uml_helpers=helpers.bin injects them
  3. At startup, uml_helpers_extract() unpacks to /tmp/uml-UMID/
  4. UML_PORT_HELPER env var is set so kernel drivers find them

The helper bundle format is a simple concatenation:
  [4 bytes magic "UMLH"][4 bytes count][count * (name\0 + 4-byte size + data)]

Signed-off-by: kerndbox <kerndbox@mixos.io>
---
 arch/um/os-Linux/Makefile         |  2 +-
 arch/um/os-Linux/helpers_embed.c  | 98 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 arch/um/os-Linux/main.c           |  4 ++
 arch/um/include/shared/os.h       |  2 ++
 4 files changed, 105 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 arch/um/os-Linux/helpers_embed.c

